#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.0"
msgid "78. Upassutisikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.78\">Monks’ Confession 78: the training rule on "
"eavesdropping</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.150
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.150\""
">Vin.4.150</a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.78.1\">Bu-Pc.78.1</a><a class"
"=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.55\">BD.3.55</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1391</a>At one "
"time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s "
"Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pesalehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ "
"bhaṇḍanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six were arguing with the good "
"monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.3"
msgid "Pesalā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "The good monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.4"
msgid "“alajjino ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū."
msgstr "“These monks from the group of six are shameless;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.5"
msgid "Na sakkā imehi saha bhaṇḍitun”ti."
msgstr "it’s not possible to argue with them.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.6"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "<p>And the monks from the group of six said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.7"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, amhe alajjivādena pāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Why are you disgracing us by calling us shameless?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.8"
msgid "“Kahaṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, assutthā”ti?"
msgstr "<p>“How did you know?”</p>"

#. VAR: upassutiṃ → upassuti (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.9"
msgid "“Mayaṃ āyasmantānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhamhā”ti."
msgstr "<p>“We were eavesdropping on you.”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.10"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1392</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.11"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

#. VAR: upassutiṃ → upassuti (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.12"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ "
"vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six eavesdrop on monks who are arguing "
"and disputing?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.13"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ "
"vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.16"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ "
"vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhissatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you eavesdrop on monks who are arguing and disputing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.17"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.18"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: upassutiṃ → upassuti (?)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:1.1.19"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ "
"upassutiṃ tiṭṭheyya—‘yaṃ ime bhaṇissanti taṃ sossāmī’ti etadeva paccayaṃ "
"karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1393</a>‘If a monk eavesdrops on monks who are arguing and disputing, "
"thinking, “I’ll hear what they say,” and he does so only for this reason and "
"no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.78.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.78.2.1\">Bu-Pc.78.2.1</a><a class=\"pts-"
"vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.56\">BD.3.56</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1394</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhūnanti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1395</a><term>On monks</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.7"
msgid "aññesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>on other monks.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.8"
msgid "Bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānanti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1396</a><term>Who are arguing and disputing</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.9"
msgid "adhikaraṇajātānaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>who are engaged in a legal issue.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7, pts-vp-pli4.151
#. VAR: Upassutiṃ → upassuti (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.10"
msgid "Upassutiṃ tiṭṭheyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1397</a><term>Eavesdrops</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"“imesaṃ sutvā codessāmi sāressāmi paṭicodessāmi paṭisāressāmi maṅkū "
"karissāmī”ti gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he is on his way to eavesdrop, thinking, “After hearing what they "
"say, I’ll accuse them/remind them/counter-accuse them/counter-remind them/"
"humiliate them,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.12"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"Wherever he stands to eavesdrop, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.13"
msgid "Pacchato gacchanto turito gacchati sossāmīti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is walking behind someone, and he speeds up with the intention to "
"eavesdrop, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.14"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"Wherever he stands to eavesdrop, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.15"
msgid "Purato gacchanto ohiyyati sossāmīti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is walking in front of someone, and he slows down with the intention "
"to eavesdrop, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.16"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"Wherever he stands to eavesdrop, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.17"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhussa ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgantvā mantentaṃ "
"ukkāsitabbaṃ, vijānāpetabbaṃ, no ce ukkāseyya vā vijānāpeyya vā, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he goes to where a monk who is speaking privately is standing, seated, or "
"lying down, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.151\">Vin.4.151</a> he should "
"clear his throat or make his presence known. If he does not clear his throat "
"or make his presence known, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.18"
msgid "Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññanti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1398</a><term>He does so only for this reason and no "
"other</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.1.19"
msgid "na añño koci paccayo hoti upassutiṃ tiṭṭhituṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>there is no other reason for eavesdropping.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.78.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.78.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1399</a>If it is one who is fully "
"ordained, and he perceives him as fully ordained, and he eavesdrops on him, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.2"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he "
"eavesdrops on him, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.3"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully "
"ordained, and he eavesdrops on him, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.4"
msgid "Anupasampannassa upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1400</a>If he eavesdrops on one who is not fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.57\""
">BD.3.57</a> wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.5"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive him as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.78.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.78.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1401</a>There is no offense:"

#. VAR: vūpasamissāmi → vūpasamessāmi (si)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"“imesaṃ sutvā oramissāmi viramissāmi vūpasamissāmi attānaṃ parimocessāmī”ti "
"gacchati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he goes, thinking, “After hearing what they say, I’ll refrain/I’ll "
"abstain/I’ll settle it/I’ll free myself;” if he is insane; if he is the "
"first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc78:2.3.3"
msgid "Upassutisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1402</a>The eighth rule, the "
"training rule on eavesdropping, is finished.</p>"
